- Updated Android Studio to 3.3.2
- Android studio opens with recent flutter projects.
- Normal project windows opened.
- Projects start syncing with gradle.
- Multiple empty, non closeable 'project windows'opens  with the android folder in its header path.
- Empty windows not listed in the Window menu. See screenshots.

comment_data.body: /cc @stevemessick

What IDE were you using to take those screenshots? Android Studio 3.3.2 does not have a floppy disk icon in its tool bar. The tool bar looks more like what was in 2.x releases. Do you have plugins installed that would reconfigure it? The screenshots indicate the Flutter plugin is not installed. I'm also puzzled why `flutter doctor -v` would find Android Studio 3.0 but not Android Studio 3.3.2.

Edit: Sorry, I found how to enable the floppy disk icon in the toolbar. But it still looks like the Flutter plugin is not installed.

Hi, sorry for the late answer.
The windows in question opens in the 3.3.2 Android Studio version.
I also have 3.0.1 installed, and sometimes they are open besides the 3.3.2 simultanously for  older projects, however no flutter project is opened in that IDE version.
In both IDE version the Flutter plugin appears in the installed plugins.

I think that the problem is linked to Gradle. Whenever gradle rebuild project the empty window appair. If the window remain visible only one is created if we minimize the empty window to dock when the gradle rebuild again a new empty window is created.

As a solution you can disable this https://w3tls.net/qx7MKib9899595f56e35786777d2c975039ce8.png
(Settings -> Languages & Frameworks -> Flutter -> Enable code completion). Uncheck it, close AS and open it again.
